Add --no-prompt flag to CLI.

Use --no-prompt to read the master password from STDIN instead of prompting.
This allows you to insert 1pass into a pipeline before a command that
expects a password on STDIN.

This command expects a PGP passphrase on STDIN:

    gpg --passphrase-fd 0

This command behaves the same, but expects a 1Password master password on
STDIN which is used to look up the PGP passphrase:

    1pass --no-prompt 'pgp-passphrase' | gpg --passphrase-fd 0
